Typically, your parents’ and grandparents’ generations would have worked for the same company for many years. It wouldn’t be uncommon to hear of someone having worked for just two companies over the duration of their career, while there are countless stories of elderly people who started and retired at the same company for their entire working life. Over the decades though, the average time people tend to stay at one job has been whittled down to four years, with millennials bucking the trend and often opting for shorter stints (generally a year or just a little more) at a time. 